# Baltic States Climate Risk Analysis — PoC

## Overview
PoC pipeline for analysing climate risks in Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania. Downloads ERA5-Land (current climate 1991-2020) and EURO-CORDEX (projections
to 2100) via the Copernicus CDS API. Computes climate risk metrics (heat days, frost days, drought days, etc.) and serves them via a Streamlit dashboard.
Status: PoC, ~10 users, all open-source.

Use open climate data from Copernicus CDS:
- ERA5-Land for the historical/reference baseline
- EURO-CORDEX for future projections

Goal:
- download and cache climate data
- compute climate risk metrics
- expose results through a lightweight user-facing interface

This project should stay beginner-friendly. At least initially, code should be heavily commented so that users with different skill levels can follow the logic.

## Architecture
Use a strict three-layer pipeline:

1. Data acquisition
   - download raw climate data from APIs
   - save raw files to `data/raw/`
   - restrict API requests to the country BBOX being processed

2. Processing and metric computation
   - clean and validate raw data
   - compute climate risk metrics
   - save processed outputs to `data/processed/`

3. Interface
   - read processed outputs only
   - do not trigger heavy recomputation from the UI layer

Keep these layers separate. Do not mix download logic, metric logic, and UI logic in the same module unless there is a very good reason.

